OL,3,COverhaul of water regulation in Wales
OL,4,Cneeded, landmark review says
OL,6,FThe system for regulating water
OL,7,Fcompanies should be overhauled and
OL,8,FNatural Resources Wales should be
OL,9,Fgiven more responsibilities, according
OL,10,Fto a landmark review of the sector.
OL,12,FA wide-ranging review into the water
OL,13,Findustry has said NRW should absorb
OL,14,Fsome of the responsibilities currently
OL,15,Fheld by the Water Services Regulation
OL,16,FAuthority, or Ofwat, which regulates
OL,17,Fthe water sector in Wales and England.
