OL,3,COverhaul of water regulation in Wales
OL,4,Cneeded, landmark review says
OL,6,FThe UK Government also supported the
OL,7,Freport, with Ms Hardy saying consumers
OL,8,Fhave been "failed time and time again".
OL,10,FSpeaking on Times Radio, she said
OL,11,F"root-and-branch reform" is needed to
OL,12,Ffix the crisis and told listeners the
OL,13,Fgovernment is considering a piece of
OL,14,Fprimary legislation to deliver many of
OL,15,Fthe proposed changes.
OL,17,FMs Hardy also described trust in the
OL,18,Fwater industry as at "the lowest ever
OL,19,Flevel" and criticised executives for
OL,20,Fhanding out pay rises and bonuses.
